-controversy-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eagainst%20ICE%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Marshall%20said%20that%20the%20store%20has%20also%20served%20as%20a%20space%20for%20the%20community%20to%20come%20in%2C%20relax%2C%20and%20process%20what%20they've%20been%20seeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRetail%20feels%20totally%20different%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Marshall%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20a%20way%20of%20connecting%20with%20our%20community%20that%20we%20haven't%20really%20felt%20before.%20It's%20very%20raw.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20part%20of%20what%20Minneapolis-area%20business%20owners%20hope%20is%20a%20temporary%20abandonment%20of%20business-as-usual.%20Since%20December%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fnews%2F2025%2F12%2F04%2Fice-arrests-worst-worst-criminal-illegal-aliens-during-operation-metro-surge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOperation%20Metro%20Surge%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20poured%20ICE%20agents%20into%20Minnesota.%20Rising%20tensions%20following%20officer%20Jonathan%20Ross's%20fatal%20shooting%20of%2037-year-old%20Renee%20Gold%20on%20January%207%20have%20further%20turned%20a%20normally%20chill%20month%20into%20a%20flurry%20of%20whistle-distributing%20and%20community%20aid.%20For%20small%20business%20owners%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20it's%20been%20an%20eventful%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20necessarily%20lucrative%20%E2%80%94%20January%2C%20as%20they%20instead%20turn%20their%20attention%20to%20supporting%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20businesses%20are%20also%20opting%20into%20a%20possible%20income%20hit%20on%20January%2023%2C%20when%20unions%20and%20faith%20leaders%20are%20calling%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafl-cio-ice-raids-minnesota-day-truth-freedom-homeland-security-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esuspension%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20school%2C%20and%20shopping%20to%20protest%20ICE's%20actions.%20Local%20news%20site%20Bring%20Me%20The%20News%20compiled%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbringmethenews.com%2Fminnesota-lifestyle%2Fgrowing-number-of-minnesota-businesses-announce-plans-to-close-for-jan-23-strike%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20over%20200%20local%20establishments'%20social%20media%20posts%20about%20their%20plans%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20economic%20blackout%20day.%20Some%20have%20said%20they%20plan%20to%20donate%20that%20day's%20revenue%3B%20others%20are%20shuttering%20completely%20or%20opening%20as%20a%20free%20community%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDHS%20Assistant%20Secretary%20Tricia%20McLaughlin%20said%20in%20a%20January%2020%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fnews%2F2026%2F01%2F20%2Fdhs-highlights-more-worst-worst-arrested-including-pedophiles-violent-assailants%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BSince%20President%20Trump%20took%20office%2C%20DHS%20has%20arrested%20over%2010%2C000%20criminal%20illegal%20aliens%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20and%20we%20are%20NOT%20slowing%20down.%20Our%20law%20enforcement%20officers%20are%20saving%20countless%20American%20lives.%26quot%3B%20ICE%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20White%20House%20spokesperson%20Abigail%20Jackson%20said%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20immigration%20operations%20%26quot%3Bhave%20resulted%20in%20countless%20dangerous%20criminal%20illegals%20being%20removed%20from%20the%20streets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaking%20American%20communities%20safer%20will%20create%20an%20environment%20in%20which%20all%20businesses%20can%20thrive%20in%20the%20long%20term%20and%20their%20customers%20can%20feel%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20Jackson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatzen%20Coffee%2C%20a%20specialty%20coffee%20shop%20with%20an%20attached%20cat%20lounge%2C%20will%20not%20be%20doing%20business%20on%20Friday%2C%20but%20plans%20to%20open%20for%20those%20who%20need%20a%20space%20to%20hang%20out%20%E2%80%94%20free%20coffee%20and%20cat%20cuddles%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatzen%20owner%20Vanessa%20Beardsley%20said%20that%20the%20irony%20of%20being%20a%20business%20owner%20and%20opting%20out%20of%20business%20for%20a%20day%20never%20crossed%20her%20mind%3B%20not%20making%20revenue%20was%20never%20part%20of%20the%20calculus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20to%20do%20what%20we%20can%20do%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Beardsley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20a%20story%20to%20tell%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220bb3222f-8e6c-462f-a5fb-38a481224b36%5C%22%3EA%20topsy-turvy%20January%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJanuary%20always%20sucks%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Cole%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Oh%20Yeah!%20Cookie%20Company%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20business%20owner%2C%20especially%20in%20retail%20business%2C%20people%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20in%20December%20and%20November%2C%20and%20they%20usually%20don't%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20in%20January.%20So%20January%20is%20always%20a%20month%20that's%20hurting%20%E2%80%94%20and%20now%20it's%20really%20hurting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENational%20Retail%20Federation's%20spending%20data%20shows%20an%20average%20drop%20in%20retail%20sales%20of%2017.3%25%20from%20December%20to%20January%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years.%20January%20through%20March%20has%20also%20typically%20seen%20the%20lowest%20average%20monthly%20employment%20for%20small%20businesses%20across%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20An%20analysis%20from%20consumer%20research%20firm%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EConsumer%20Edge%20of%20credit%20and%20debit%20card%20data%20found%20that%20spending%20in%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMinneapolis-St.%20Paul%20metro%20area%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eby%20households%20earning%20under%20%24100%2C000%20has%20tracked%20lower%20than%20the%20national%20average%20over%20the%20four%20weeks%20ending%20January%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUwHNn%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUwHNn%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20Cole%20estimates%20he's%20donated%20around%20%24300%20worth%20of%20cookies%20to%20groups%20distributing%20treats%20to%20kids%20who%20can't%20go%20to%20school%20amid%20ICE's%20presence.%20He%20said%20that%20if%20he%20does%20make%20any%20money%20right%20now%2C%20he'll%20donate%2010%25%20of%20his%20sales.%20The%20full-time%20role%20he%20works%20in%20addition%20to%20his%20homemade%20baking%20business%20has%20been%20keeping%20him%20afloat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECole%20isn't%20the%20only%20one%20pivoting%20from%20normal%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJP%20Pritchett%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20adult%20store%20Smitten%20Kitten%20in%20Minneapolis%2C%20said%20that%20they%20usually%20devote%20January%20to%20ramping%20up%20for%20Valentine's%20Day%2C%20which%20they%20described%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BSuper%20Bowl%26quot%3B%20for%20adult%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTypically%20in%20January%2C%20we're%20ramping%20up%20inventory%2C%20getting%20the%20store%20stocked%2C%20just%20getting%20ready%20to%20do%20commerce%2C%26quot%3B%20Pritchett%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20year%2C%20I%20don't%20care%20about%20that.%20Nobody%20cares%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Pritchett%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20stopped%20all%20regular%20business%20and%20created%20a%20free%20store%20inside%20Smitten%20Kitten%20where%20people%20could%20come%20get%20fo